description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to internal promotion we have an exciting opportunity for you to join our catering management team. Are you passionate about food and want to make a difference to our patient’s and staff meal experience? Then this may be the job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandwell &amp; West Birmingham NHS Trust in house catering services are looking to recruit an experienced band 4 Catering Manager primarily based at City Hospital with the ability to work across sites at Sandwell and Rowley Regis hospitals. This is a full time position Monday to Friday although may involve the occasional weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will report to the site Catering Manager and will be responsible for assisting in the daily delivery of the patient and staff meal service and associated catering staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In conjunction with the site catering manager the day to day responsibility for providing a high quality catering service to patients, staff and visitors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in responsibility for completion of staff rosters, staff welfare, training and performance management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insure SLA and KPI are set and met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Input into managing and maintaining site budgets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduction of waste&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the delivery of the trusts sustainability catering strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To meet food safety requirements and comply with HACCP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with planning and development of retail menus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organisation, communication and customer services skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good level of computer literacy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of delivering objectives and targets on time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This provides an exciting opportunity for a talented and passionate Assistant Catering Manager to come onboard and join the team to deliver excellent standards of catering and hospitality&lt;/p&gt;
